<section class="page-section anchor" id="aphasia">
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-tag red">1.04</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Cortical Signs — Aphasia & Frontal Lobe</h2>
  </div>

  <h3>⭐ Cortical Signs Definitions</h3>
  <div class="tbl-wrap">
    <table>
      <tr><th>Sign</th><th>Definition</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Aphasia</td><td>Inability to understand or express words despite intact sensorimotor pathways</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Agnosia</td><td>Inability to understand meaning of sensory stimuli despite intact sensory pathways</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Apraxia</td><td>Inability to perform voluntary acts despite intact motor, sensory, and mental status — patient is awake but cannot perform learned movements</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Agraphia</td><td>Inability to write — Left parietal, angular gyrus</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Acalculia</td><td>Difficulty with math — Left parietal, angular gyrus</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Alexia</td><td>"Word blindness" — can see words, cannot interpret meaning</td></tr>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h3>⭐ Types of Aphasia (F=Fluency, C=Comprehension, R=Repetition)</h3>
  <div class="tbl-wrap">
    <table>
      <tr><th>Aphasia</th><th>F</th><th>C</th><th>R</th><th>Naming</th><th>Location</th><th>Classic Description</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Global</td><td class="hl-red">✗</td><td class="hl-red">✗</td><td class="hl-red">✗</td><td>Poor</td><td>Entire perisylvian area</td><td>Most severe — all language modalities impaired</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Mixed Transcortical</td><td class="hl-red">✗</td><td class="hl-red">✗</td><td class="hl">✓</td><td>Poor</td><td>Perisylvian cortex (ant &amp; post)</td><td>Like global but CAN repeat</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl" style="background:#fff3e0">Broca's ⭐</td><td class="hl-red">✗</td><td class="hl">✓</td><td class="hl-red">✗</td><td>Poor</td><td>Left posterior inferior frontal operculum</td><td>Non-fluent; telegraphic speech ("Want cookie"); understands; frustrated</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Transcortical Motor</td><td class="hl-red">✗</td><td class="hl">✓</td><td class="hl">✓</td><td>Normal</td><td>Frontally + superiorly → striatum</td><td>Broca's that can repeat</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl" style="background:#fff3e0">Wernicke's ⭐</td><td class="hl">✓</td><td class="hl-red">✗</td><td class="hl-red">✗</td><td>Poor</td><td>Posterior perisylvian, temporal operculum</td><td>Fluent but meaningless "Word Salad"; poor comprehension</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Transcortical Sensory</td><td class="hl">✓</td><td class="hl-red">✗</td><td class="hl">✓</td><td>Normal</td><td>Parietal/temporal, thalamocortical circuit</td><td>Wernicke's that can repeat</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Conduction</td><td class="hl">✓</td><td class="hl">✓</td><td class="hl-red">✗</td><td>Poor</td><td>Posterior perisylvian (arcuate fasciculus)</td><td>Fluent, understands, CANNOT repeat</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Anomic</td><td class="hl">✓</td><td class="hl">✓</td><td class="hl">✓</td><td>Poor</td><td>Angular gyrus</td><td>Cannot name objects; everything else intact</td></tr>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="callout yellow"><strong>⭐ Algorithm</strong> Is speech fluent? → YES: comprehend? → Wernicke's / Transcortical Sensory / Conduction / Anomic | NO: comprehend? → Broca's / Transcortical Motor / Global / Mixed. Repetition separates transcortical from non-transcortical.</div>

  <h3>Destructive vs Irritative Lesions ⭐</h3>
  <div class="compare">
    <div class="compare-col">
      <div class="compare-col-head red">Destructive Lesion</div>
      <div class="compare-col-body">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Loss</strong> of function</li>
          <li>FEF (e.g., stroke): eyes look <strong>TOWARD</strong> the lesion</li>
          <li>PPRF: eyes can't look <strong>AWAY</strong> from lesion (ipsilateral gaze palsy)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="compare-col">
      <div class="compare-col-head teal">Irritative Lesion</div>
      <div class="compare-col-body">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Promotes/Stimulates</strong> function</li>
          <li>FEF (e.g., seizure focus): eyes look <strong>AWAY</strong> from (contralateral to) lesion</li>
          <li>Preferential gaze = HARD SIGN (cannot fake)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

