<section class="page-section anchor" id="gaze">
  <div class="section-header">
    <span class="section-tag red">1.04</span>
    <h2 class="section-title">Gaze Pathway & Pupils</h2>
  </div>

  <h3>⭐ Horizontal Gaze Pathway</h3>
  <div class="callout blue"><strong>Normal:</strong> Right FEF → decussates → Left PPRF → Left CN VI (lateral rectus, left eye abducts) → via MLF to Right CN III (medial rectus, right eye adducts) → GAZE TO THE LEFT.</div>

  <div class="tbl-wrap">
    <table>
      <tr><th>Area</th><th>Function</th><th>Destructive Lesion → Gaze</th><th>Irritative Lesion → Gaze</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">FEF (BA 8) ⭐</td><td>Sends signals to contralateral PPRF</td><td>TOWARD lesion (ipsilateral)</td><td>AWAY from lesion (contralateral)</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">PPRF ⭐</td><td>Facilitates horizontal saccades ipsilaterally</td><td>AWAY from lesion (ipsilateral gaze palsy)</td><td>TOWARD lesion</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">MLF</td><td>Connects PPRF to contralateral CN III (medial rectus)</td><td>INO: impaired adduction ipsilateral eye + contralateral nystagmus</td><td>TOWARD lesion</td></tr>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="callout yellow"><strong>⭐ Internuclear Ophthalmoplegia (INO)</strong> MLF lesion → Ipsilateral eye cannot ADDUCT + Contralateral eye NYSTAGMUS on abduction + CONVERGENCE preserved. Common in MS (bilateral INO = bilateral MLF lesion).</div>

  <h3>⭐ Cavernous Sinus Contents</h3>
  <div class="callout teal"><strong>CN III, IV, V1, V2, VI</strong> + Internal carotid artery + Optic chiasm nearby + Pituitary gland nearby.<br>If CN III + IV + V1 + V2 + VI all involved → Cavernous sinus syndrome. No other single location houses all these nerves together!</div>

  <h3>Brainstem CN Localization</h3>
  <div class="tbl-wrap">
    <table>
      <tr><th>Level</th><th>Cranial Nerves</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Midbrain</td><td>CN III, IV</td><td>CN III emerges at interpeduncular fossa; CN IV = only CN that exits dorsally</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Pons</td><td>CN V, VI, VII, VIII</td><td>Gaze palsy + lower face (LMN) = pons</td></tr>
      <tr><td class="hl">Medulla</td><td>CN IX, X, XI, XII</td><td>Wallenberg (PICA), medial medullary (ASA)</td></tr>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

