<div class="mcq" id="q1">
  <div class="mcq-num">Question 1</div>
  <div class="mcq-q">Which layer of the cerebral cortex contains Betz cells, and what is their primary function?</div>
  <div class="mcq-opts">
    <div class="mcq-opt" onclick="answer(this,'q1',false)"><span class="letter">A</span> Layer IV — Internal Granule Cell Layer; receives thalamic input</div>
    <div class="mcq-opt" onclick="answer(this,'q1',true)"><span class="letter">B</span> Layer V — Internal Pyramidal Cell Layer; major output layer via corticospinal tract for motor control</div>
    <div class="mcq-opt" onclick="answer(this,'q1',false)"><span class="letter">C</span> Layer VI — Multiform Layer; diverse cell types for sensory integration</div>
    <div class="mcq-opt" onclick="answer(this,'q1',false)"><span class="letter">D</span> Layer III — External Pyramidal Cell Layer; receives input from contralateral cortex</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mcq-explain" id="q1-exp">Betz cells are found in Layer V (Internal Pyramidal Cell Layer). They are the largest neurons in the cortex and are responsible for supplying the corticospinal tract for voluntary motor control. Layer V = major output layer of the cerebral cortex.</div>
