  <div class="mcq-q">Which of the following correctly describes the Brudzinski sign?</div>
  <div class="mcq-opts">
    <div class="mcq-opt" onclick="answer(this,'q20',false)"><span class="letter">A</span> Passive knee extension from 90° hip flexion causes pain → meningeal irritation</div>
    <div class="mcq-opt" onclick="answer(this,'q20',false)"><span class="letter">B</span> The patient actively flexes their neck, causing hip and knee flexion</div>
    <div class="mcq-opt" onclick="answer(this,'q20',true)"><span class="letter">C</span> Passive neck flexion by examiner causes involuntary hip and knee flexion</div>
    <div class="mcq-opt" onclick="answer(this,'q20',false)"><span class="letter">D</span> Pressing the cheek causes facial muscle contraction</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mcq-explain" id="q20-exp">Brudzinski sign: PASSIVE neck flexion by EXAMINER → involuntary hip and knee flexion. This is due to meningeal irritation. Memory trick: "Batok = Brudzinski" (batok = back of neck in Filipino). Kernig = "Ker-knee": PASSIVE knee extension from 90° hip flex → pain/resistance. Both tests are PASSIVE (examiner performs the movement).</div>
</div>
